169 (b) Any food service establishment that unknowingly
170 violates this article due to a good faith reliance upon the
171 establishment's supplier's attestation of the covered
172 commodity's country of origin shall be held harmless against
173 penalties for a violation of this article.
174 (c) A food service establishment may appeal any penalty
175 assessed pursuant to this section in accordance with the
176 Alabama Administrative Procedure Act. Judicial review of a
177 final action of the department shall be pursuant to Section
178 41-22-20.
179 (d) All fines and other monies collected pursuant to
180 this section shall be distributed to the department and used
181 to implement, enforce, and administer this article.
182 (e) The State Health Officer or Attorney General may
183 file an action to collect any unpaid penalty levied pursuant
184 to this section in a court of competent jurisdiction. The
185 defendant establishment shall be liable for all costs
186 associated with the collection of any unpaid penalty.
187 (f) The State Health Officer shall regularly publish
188 the names and addresses of all food service establishments
189 that violate this article.
190 (g) A score or grade issued or assigned pursuant to
191 Section 22-20-5 to any food service establishment that
192 violates this article shall be reduced by five points for the
193 time period of the score or grade."
194 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
195 1, 2026.
